{"comments":"Typographic length units.\n\nUnits specific to typography, print, and digital publishing.\n\n## Historical Context\n- Point: Originally varied by country/foundry. PostScript standardized\n  at exactly 1/72 inch. CSS uses PostScript points.\n- Pica: 12 points, from metal typesetting.\n- Didot: European point system, still used in continental Europe.\n- Cicero: 12 Didot points, European pica equivalent.\n\n## Modern Usage\nPostScript/DTP points (1/72 inch) are the de facto standard for digital\ntypography. Didot points persist in European book publishing.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[117,29],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typographic.purs","start":[117,15]},"title":"Point"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Physical","Typographic"],"Point"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[119,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typographic.purs","start":[119,1]},"title":"eqPoint"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Physical","Typographic"],"Point"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[120,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typographic.purs","start":[120,1]},"title":"ordPoint"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Physical","Typographic"],"Point"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[123,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typographic.purs","start":[122,1]},"title":"showPoint"}],"comments":"Point - 1/72 inch (PostScript/DTP standard)\n\nThe PostScript point is exactly 1/72 inch = 0.3527... mm.\nThis is the universal standard for digital typography.\n\nHistorical note: The traditional printer's point was 1/72.27 inch\n(0.3514... mm), but PostScript simplified to exactly 1/72.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[117,29],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typographic.purs","start":[117,1]},"title":"Point"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[144,27],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typographic.purs","start":[144,14]},"title":"Pica"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Physical","Typographic"],"Pica"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[146,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typographic.purs","start":[146,1]},"title":"eqPica"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Physical","Typographic"],"Pica"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[147,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Physical/Typograph